BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:b8q5G0V4ChtT9N5fukGse
SUMMARY:Immigration is Not Invasion: Dean's Luminaries in Law Series with I
	lya Somin
DTSTAMP:20260318T065003Z
DTSTART:20260319T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Seattle University School of Law’s Luminaries in Law Series con
	tinues with a timely and thought-provoking conversation titled Immigration
	 Is Not Invasion\, featuring renowned constitutional law scholar Ilya Somi
	n.\n\n \n\nIn this special lunchtime event\, Professor Somin will be inter
	viewed by Anthony E. Varona\, Dean of Seattle University School of Law\, a
	nd Andrew Siegel\, Professor of Law. Together\, they will explore Professo
	r Somin’s scholarship challenging the increasingly common framing of immig
	ration as an “invasion\,” examining its constitutional\, historical\, and 
	democratic implications.\n\n \n\nThe discussion will engage questions at t
	he intersection of immigration law\, constitutional structure\, political 
	rhetoric\, and civil liberties\, offering insight into how legal doctrine 
	and public discourse shape immigration policy and democratic values. Drawi
	ng on their respective expertise\, Dean Varona and Professor Siegel will g
	uide a wide-ranging conversation designed to illuminate one of the most pr
	essing legal and societal debates of our time.\n\n \n\nStudents\, faculty\
	, and members of the broader legal community are invited to attend this en
	gaging installment of the Luminaries in Law series.\n\n \n\nDate: March 19
	th\n\nLocation: Room C5\, Sullivan Hall\n\nTime: 12:00 PM to 12:50 PM.\n\n
	https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/immigration-is-not-invasion-
	dean-s-luminaries-in-law-series-with-ilya-somin/18260246/2026-03-19T00\n\n
	From SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/immigration-is-not-invasi
	on-dean-s-luminaries-in-law-series-with-ilya-somin/18260246/2026-03-19T00
LOCATION:Sullivan Hall\, C5\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT50M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:938OonTzypZ3ldQylqvcy
SUMMARY:Free Virtual Sessions for Adoption
DTSTAMP:20260318T065003Z
DTSTART:20260319T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Northwest Adoption Exchange \\(NWAE\\) is inviting all those in
	terested in adopting from foster care to attend free\, virtual information
	 sessions to learn about the process.\n\nOffered in partnership with the W
	ashington State Department of Children\, Youth\, and Families \\(DCYF\\)\,
	 these sessions provide guidance and clarity for anyone beginning or conti
	nuing their adoption journey.\n\nWho: Open to anyone interested in adoptin
	g from foster care in Washington state.\n\nWhat: Free virtual information 
	sessions on the adoption process.\n\nWhen: Monthly sessions\, participants
	 are encouraged to attend Session 1 before attending Session 2.  Upcoming 
	dates:\n\n·         Session 1: March 5 at 12 p.m. or 6 p.m.\n\n·         S
	ession 2: March 19 at 12 p.m. or 6 p.m.\n\nWhere: Online\, register at nwa
	e.org\n\nCost: Free\n\nLed by experienced child welfare professionals\, NW
	AE’s sessions are presented virtually in two parts and offer a comprehensi
	ve introduction to adoption. Participants will gain insights into the need
	s of youth waiting for permanent families and learn how to navigate each s
	tage of the adoption journey with confidence.\n\nSession 1: Introduction t
	o adoption from foster care Explore how adoption fits into the foster care
	 system\, the types of support available\, and what to consider when deter
	mining if adoption is right for your family.\n\nSession 2: The steps to ad
	option Walk through the practical aspects of adoption\, from choosing an a
	gency and completing required training to navigating the home study proces
	s.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-virtual-sessions-
	for-adoption/18153261/2026-03-19T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-virtual-sessions-for
	-adoption/18153261/2026-03-19T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:I84iiMzxjtAZjk1GIsRq2
SUMMARY:Susan Meiselas: Crossings
DTSTAMP:20260318T065003Z
DTSTART:20260319T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:First presented at the Art Institute of Chicago in 1990\, this 
	exhibition by Susan Meiselas intertwines documentary photographs of Centra
	l America during the 1970s and 1980s \\(from Nicaragua and El Salvador\\) 
	along with panoramic images from the US/Mexico border taken in 1989. Addit
	ional photographs of the US/Mexico border taken in 2018 are also featured 
	in a site-specific gallery installation. The exhibition invites viewers to
	 see immigration in the context of economic and political crises in the re
	gion.\n\nToday\, the work feels newly urgent. US immigration enforcement h
	as expanded through militarization and constant surveillance\, with leader
	s using fear-driven language to divide communities and legitimize brutal f
	orms of control.\n\nThese photographs ask us to look carefully\, to recogn
