UID:EwMJRTjHbQG-M5xmJcm9e
SUMMARY:Tammy the Troll\, A Dance in the Forest
DTSTAMP:20260318T065005Z
DTSTART:20260329T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Neighborhoods: Alki/Admiral\,Arbor Heights\,Ballard\,Beacon Hil
	l\,Belltown\,Broadview/Bitter Lake\,Capitol Hill\,Cascade/Eastlake/So uth 
	Lake Union\,Cedar Park/Meadowbrook\,Central Area/Squire Park\,Chinat own-I
	nternational District\,Citywide\,Columbia City\,Crown Hill\,Delridg e/Nort
	h Delridge\,Downtown Commercial Core\,Duwamish/SODO\,East of Seatt le\,Fau
	ntleroy/Morgan Junction/Seaview\,First Hill\,Fremont\,Georgetown \,Green L
	ake\,Greenwood/Phinney Ridge\,Haller Lake\,High Point\,Highland Park\,Inte
	rbay\,Judkins Park\,Lake City/Olympic Hills/Victory Heights\,L aurelhurst/
	Sand Point\,Licton Springs\,Madison Park\,Madrona/Leschi\,Mag nolia\,Mille
	r Park\,Montlake/Portage Bay\,Mt. Baker/North Rainier\,North Beach/Blue Ri
	dge\,North Beacon Hill/Jefferson Park\,North Capitol Hill \,North of Seatt
	le\,Northgate/Maple Leaf\,Online Event\,Pioneer Square\,Q ueen Anne\,Raini
	er Beach/Othello\,Ravenna/Bryant/Roosevelt\,Riverview\,R oxhill/Westwood/W
	hite Center\,Seward Park\,South Beacon Hill/New Holly\, South of Seattle\,
	South Park\,Sunset Hill/Loyal Heights\,University Dist rict\,Uptown\,Walli
	ngford\,Wedgwood/View Ridge\,West of Seattle\,West Se attle Junction/Genes
	ee Hill\,Whittier Heights\n\nEvent Types: Arts\,Comm unity\,Dance\,Theater
	\,Youth\n\nAudience: Adults\,All\,Children\,Family \,Senior\,Special Needs
	\,Teen\n\nSponsoring Organization: Variety Plus Th eater\n\nContact: Angel
	a Rinaldi\n\nContact Phone: \\(206\\) 819-6039\n\nContact Email: vptheater
	@aol.com\n\nPre-Register: No\n\nCost: $20 General Admission\n\nRegistratio
	n Details: Online tickets at: https://www.varietyplus.org/performancesTick
	ets also available at the door\n\nLink: https://www.varietyplus.org\n\nA n
	ew musical adaptation! Featuring 33 Seattle area youth\n\nBased on the boo
	k: Tammy the Troll\, A Dance in the Forest by Dina McDermott\n\nWritten an
	d directed by Bob Gribas\n\nOriginal Music by Angela Rinaldi-Gribas\n\nCho
	reography by Dina McDermott\n\nThe Story\n\nA curious group of friends ven
	tures into the heart of the forest in search of Tammy the Troll-a shy lege
	nd whispered about but never truly known. Their path winds beneath glisten
	ing spider webs\, through knotted roots and towering mountains\, and along
	 the swif t\, laughing currents of the river. Guided and aided by the fore
	st's magical residents-Spiders\, Talking Trees\, the Foothill Folk \, clev
	er Mice\, and playful River Tributaries-the friends press on. Every challe
	nge draws them closer\, proving that the greatest reward of the journey is
	 not just reaching Tammy\, but discovering the beginnings of a lasting fri
	endship.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tammy-the-troll-
	a-dance-in-the-forest/18329051/2026-03-29T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tammy-the-troll-a-dance-i
	n-the-forest/18329051/2026-03-29T00
LOCATION:Seattle Center\, 305 Harrison St\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
